President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Andrew Jackson as the Assistant Secretary for Management at the Department of Education. Jackson is currently the Deputy Assistant Secretary for Technology, Information, and Business Services at the Department of the Interior. He has previously held positions at Hewlett-Packard and worked as a corporate transactional attorney. Jackson holds a B.A. from the University of Miami, a J.D. from Harvard Law School, and an M.B.A. from the Wharton Business School at the University of Pennsylvania.

President Obama has also appointed Robert J. Glovsky and Deanna M. Mulligan as members of the President's Advisory Council on Financial Capability for Young Americans. Glovsky is currently the Vice Chair and a Principal of The Colony Group and has previously served as a founder and President of Mintz Levin Financial Advisors. Mulligan is the President and CEO of The Guardian Life Insurance Company of America and has held various positions at Guardian Life and other insurance companies. Glovsky holds a B.A. from Dartmouth College and an LL.M and a J.D. from Boston University School of Law, while Mulligan received a B.A. from the University of Nebraska and an M.B.A. from Stanford University Graduate School of Business.